items.name: Residential Service
items.description:
Single-phase, 60-cycle, alternating current service to residential units including separately metered
apartments, private rooming houses, and fraternity and sorority houses for lighting, cooking, heating,
ordinary household appliances, motors of 7.5 horsepower or less individual capacity, and all appliances which do not interfere with lighting service. The applicable commercial lighting and power rate schedules will apply to the common portion of multi-dwelling buildings when the apartments are separately metered, and to electric space-heating service furnished to such buildings if the apartments are not separately metered.
items.energycomments: Customer charge is determined by the daily service charge: $0.62466*365.25=$228.157065/12 months=$19.01308875
